description: Irish Foreign Affairs Minister Simon Coveney says a specialised committee will meet again on Friday.
title: NI Brexit: Simon Coveney says there is time to resolve issues
title_page: NI Brexit: Simon Coveney says there is time to resolve issues - BBC News
maintext: The Brexit withdrawal deal means the UK and EU joint committee have to assess what goods going from GB to NI are deemed to be "at risk" of being exported to the EU and should therefore have tariffs - taxes on imports - imposed on them.
